// SU-1 (techdesign-stream-unsubscribe.md §7 T2/T4): a one-shot program that
// subscribes to a signal under `using` and lets the scope close it. The last
// subscriber leaving unwatches + closes the signalfd (R6), so no live watch
// pins the event loop — the program drains and EXITS on its own with no signal
// ever sent. Before SU-1, signal::on left the fd/watch alive for the whole run
// and this program would hang forever. Also exercises `using` teardown on the
// ordinary fall-through edge.
void watch() {
    using InStream<int> w = signal::on(signal::WINCH);
    console.writeln("subscribed");
}
watch();
console.writeln("after-scope");
